<paragraph blockId="20.[144,759,1422,1566]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
<emphasis box="[144,269,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is an invariable substantive in apposition, which refers to the colloquial name ‘mila’ of my mother (M. A. M.), to whom M. A. M. dedicates this new species as a sign of gratitude for teaching a love of insects.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[144,759,1605,1903]" lastBlockId="20.[806,1422,198,618]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
<emphasis box="[144,342,1606,1627]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be separated easily by the following characters: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[323,485,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis box="[323,485,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the eye suture 2¥ length of ocellar triangle and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[517,619,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[517,619,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
more than 2.5 ¥; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[218,382,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis box="[218,382,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has all the hairs of mesonotum yellow and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[275,371,1758,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[275,371,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the mesonotum with hairs of two colours, yellow in the anterior and posterior part and a wide transversal band of black hairs in the middle; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[242,410,1850,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis box="[242,410,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the posterior anepisternum mainly yellow and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[441,541,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[441,541,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the posterior anepisternum mainly black. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1135,1338,198,219]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[1135,1338,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Copestylum milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have sternite 2 and the anterior part of sternite 3 completely yellow but 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[1203,1369,259,280]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis box="[1203,1369,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has black spots in the middle of these sternites. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">Copestylum quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the epandrium in ventral view less than 2¥ as long as broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[806,1422,198,618]" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">
The early stages of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1061,1157,381,403]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[1061,1157,381,403]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of spicules on the anterodorsal margin of the mesothorax. Of other Apiciferum group species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[977,1074,473,495]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[977,1074,473,495]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="717">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be separated from it by the AP, which is as long as the TR is wide and the openings of the pupal spiracles clustered on the apex rather than being spread down the sides.
</paragraph>
